                     </persName>
                  , Esq. by the name and description of Messrs. Hoare, for the sum of 96 l.
            </rs> the tenor of which false, forged, and counterfeited order for payment, is as follows; that is to say,</p>

               <p>"Gentlemen, pay</p>
               <p>"the bearer 96 l. yours 
               <persName id="t17920704-5-person111">
                  George
                   Hardinge
               <interp inst="t17920704-5-person111" type="surname" value="Hardinge"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17920704-5-person111" type="given" value="George"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17920704-5-person111" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            ,</p>
               <p>"April the 11th, 1792; Messrs. Hoare." with intention to defraud the said 
               
                  <persName id="t17920704-5-victim113" type="victimName">
                     Henry 
                     Hoare
                  <interp inst="t17920704-5-victim113" type="surname" value="Hoare"></interp>
